description: Enforce one context per file for React features and Rust Tauri modules
alwaysApply: true
---

# Spaghetti Checker — One Context Per File

Keep each file focused on a single responsibility. Too much in one file (TMI) hurts
readability, reviewability, and testability.

---

## Frontend `src/`

```
src/
  app/                   # App shell, providers, routing entry
  features/<name>/       # route-level pages (one page per file)
  components/<area>/     # reusable UI (one component per .tsx)
  controllers/           # gamepad + spatial focus (one concern per file)
  hooks/                 # one hook per file
  stores/                # Zustand slices (one store per file)
  themes/                # built-in theme shells + layout hooks
  lib/                   # pure helpers, Tauri wrappers, formatters
  types/                 # shared TypeScript types
  e2e/                   # Playwright tests (repo root)
```

| File | Allowed contents |
| ---- | ---------------- |
| `features/*/*.tsx` | Single page/screen component |
| `components/*/*.tsx` | Single reusable component |
| `hooks/*.ts` | Single custom hook |
| `stores/*.store.ts` | Single Zustand store |
| `controllers/*.ts` | Single controller/focus concern |
| `app/App.tsx` | Screen routing + layout wiring only — no heavy business logic |

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — inline importer logic inside a page
export function LibraryPage() {
  const scanSteam = async () => { /* 80 lines */ }
  return (...)
}

// ✅ GOOD — page composes hooks and components
export function LibraryPage() {
  const { games } = useGames()
  return <GameGrid games={games} />
}
```

Cross-feature shared UI → `src/components/`. Feature-specific UI stays in
`src/features/<name>/` or colocated components under `src/components/<area>/`.

---

## Backend `src-tauri/src/`

```
src-tauri/src/
  commands/              # one Tauri command group per file (*.rs)
  database/              # migrations + repository
  importers/             # one importer per platform
  launching/             # launcher, process monitor, session
  models/                # shared Rust structs
  services/              # orchestration (library sync, artwork)
  utils/                 # path helpers, filename parsing, size
```

| File | Allowed contents |
| ---- | ---------------- |
| `commands/*.rs` | Tauri `#[tauri::command]` handlers for one domain |
| `importers/*.rs` | Single platform importer |
| `database/repository.rs` | SQLite access — no launch/process logic |
| `launching/*.rs` | Process lifecycle only |

```rust
// ❌ BAD — command file mixes DB, import, and launch
#[tauri::command]
async fn do_everything() { /* ... */ }

// ✅ GOOD — thin command delegates to service/importer
#[tauri::command]
fn scan_steam_library(state: State<'_, AppState>) -> Result<Vec<Game>, String> {
    steam::scan(&state.repo)
}
```

Register commands in `lib.rs` via `generate_handler!` — keep `lib.rs` as wiring only.

---

## When to split

Split when a file has **more than one** of: page, component, hook, store, Tauri command
group, importer, service concern, or adapter.

---

## Tests

- **Rust:** unit tests in the same module (`#[cfg(test)]`) or `src-tauri/tests/`.
  Run `yarn run test:rust`.
- **E2E:** Playwright in `e2e/*.spec.ts`. Run `yarn run test:e2e` for UI/navigation changes.
- Prefer adding E2E coverage for new screens and controller flows.

---

## Agent checklist (run on every create/modify)

When creating or editing under `src/` or `src-tauri/src/`:

1. **Match layout** — use the canonical folder tree above.
2. **Split before merge** — new screen → `features/`; new command group → `commands/`; new importer → `importers/`.
3. **Run gates** — `yarn run typecheck`, `yarn run test:rust` (Rust), `yarn run test:e2e` (UI).
4. **Update docs** — README architecture section or `docs/THEMES.md` if structure or theme contract changed.
